      <h3>The International Organization for Adolescents (IOFA):</h3>

<ul>
	<li>Builds institutional capacity to address complex child and adolescent welfare issues</li>
	<li>Works holistically to coordinate stakeholders in social service, law enforcement, the courts, healthcare, and other systems</li>
	<li>Advances evidence-based program design and groundbreaking research</li>
	<li>Develops scalable and replicable project models</li>
	<li>Operates with minimal infrastructure to maximize local ownership</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Over its 15-year history, IOFA has implemented 35 projects in 23 countries. For more information, see <a href="http://iofa.dev/our-work/our-projects">Our Projects</a>.</strong></p>

